вҸә This is a known issue. Claude Code's native ghostty notification channel is broken on macOS (tracked in anthropics/claude-code#19979).

  The fix: Set preferredNotifChannel to "iterm2" вҖ” Ghostty correctly interprets iTerm2-compatible OSC sequences, so notifications work through that
  channel.

  Let me check your current setting and apply the fix.

  Read 1 file (ctrl+o to expand)

вҸә I can see the issue. Your notification hook uses \e]9; (OSC 9) which is the right idea, but this doesn't work with Ghostty's notification
  implementation. You also don't have preferredNotifChannel set, so Claude Code defaults to auto which likely picks the broken ghostty channel.

  Let me fix both:

  Read 1 file (ctrl+o to expand)

вҸә Two changes needed:

  1. Add "preferredNotifChannel": "iterm2" so Claude Code's built-in notifications work
  2. Update the hook to use iTerm2's OSC 9 protocol properly (with \033]9; which Ghostty supports via iTerm2 compatibility)

